      "identifier": "upload_error_classification_mismatch",
      "summary": "Upload validation errors are over-bucketed as unauthorized, mixing auth failures with internal/runtime failures.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`validateUploadRequest` can return auth errors and internal dependency/runtime errors, but `HTTPUploadHandler` maps all validation failures to `http.StatusUnauthorized`.",
        "Pipeline fallback maps unclassified failures to `http.StatusBadRequest`, including non-client causes, creating inconsistent failure semantics across adjacent paths."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define typed/sentinel upload errors (authn, authz, validation, transient infra, internal misconfiguration) and centralize status mapping so auth errors map to 401/403, client input to 400, and internal/runtime faults to 5xx.",
