      "evidence": [
        "`check502Loop` repeatedly logs operational errors (`GetShipStatusFn`, `LoadUrbitConfigFn`, HTTP polling) and continues indefinitely without a terminal error path.",
        "`CheckVersionLoopWithContext` and `OldLogsCleanerWithContext` count consecutive failures and return explicit errors after threshold, surfacing sustained degradation."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Standardize loop error policy across subsystems: shared consecutive-failure budget, optional backoff, and explicit terminal/health signal behavior. Apply to 502 loop so persistent outages become observable and actionable.",
